      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW HADES (7) scored (21.97) last time out at Ballarat adding to an already respectable career. Hard to go past form at this journey. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Looks the testing material. PROCYON (1) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (22.85) at Geelong over 400m. Deserves a win and gets her chance. AVENTIS (2) jumps from box 2 for the first time after placing latest at Geelong (22.80) in a Bottom Up - Grade 6. The form from her last run stacks up well. Expecting another good run. PORANGI MOOSE (6) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
